The electrocatalytic reaction of diclofenac and DDPM was explored using different electrodes by cyclic voltammetric method (Fig. 3
                        ). The NiO-SWCNTs/DDPM/CPE show a quasi-reversible (ΔEp = 600 mV) in buffer solution and in the absence of diclofenac (curve a). After addition of 500 μM diclofenac to solution (phosphate buffer solution pH = 8.0) and at a surface of NiO-SWCNTs/DDPM/CPE, the oxidation signal of DDPM increased and reduction signal of mediator reduced simultaneously. This phenomenon confirms an EC/ reaction of DDPM and diclofenac at NiO-SWCNTs/DDPM/CPE surface (Scheme 1
                        ).
